Class IACP

    java.lang.Runnable

    public class IACP
extends java.lang.Thread
    This class manages an ISI style connection. It does the Raw IO and returns packets on the link

    • Constructor Detail

      • IACP

        public IACP(java.lang.String h,
    int p,
    java.lang.String stat,
    int procid,
    int to,
    int sndsize,
    int rcvsize,
    int throttle,
    java.lang.String bind,
    EdgeThread parent)
        Creates a new instance of IACP
        Parameters:
        h - host string to contact
        p - Port on that host with a ISI server
        stat - The station or more practically the loop name
        procid - The process id to use to set up the IACP
        to - The time out per ISI manual for reconnects/heartbeats for the IACP
        sndsize - The buffer send size for the IACP
        rcvsize - The buffer rcv size for the IACP
        throttle - The throttle b/s to be enforced by the IACP
        bind - Bind IP address (or null for none)
        parent - The parent to log through.
